author: @sumanpalisetty6096
comment:
git is not a recognised command

Locate your Git installation folder — usually
C:\Program Files\Git\bin
or
C:\Program Files\Git\cmd

Copy that path.

Press Windows + R → type “sysdm.cpl” → Enter.

Go to Advanced → Environment Variables.

Under System variables, select Path → Edit → New → Paste Git path.

Click OK → restart your Command Prompt.
